  "text": "on M ⊕M ⊕M and we also refer to J = Λ⊗J as being generated by J. Since J is a symplectic structure, Λ ⊗ J is skew symmetric, but its nondegeneracy must be established for it to be a symplectic structure. Eirola et. al. [CITATION_1] have shown it to be symplectic for the symmetric OLM's. However, we are not concerned with this issue here and will broadly refer to Λ ⊗ J as a symplectic structure.",
